media$title.$t: Deaf Winterfest 3 Commercial: Part Three

media$description.$t: DEAF Inc is hosting their 3rd Annual Deaf Winterfest (DWF3), where at DWF3, deaf, hard of hearing and hearing people get together to celebrate their deafness and culture. There's plenty of social opportunities, broomball tournament, exhibition booths, VIP dinner and DeFrost (End-of-Winter party). We're loaded with deaf awareness for hearing community to learn about deaf and hard of hearing community. DWF3 raises funds for DEAF Inc.'s deaf and hard of hearing programs. We hope that we will see you all at DWF3!

title.$t: Deaf Winterfest 3

media$title.$t: Deaf Winterfest 3

media$description.$t:
DEAF Inc. present their 3rd annual, Deaf Winterfest (DWF3). It will be held at Webster Groves Recreation Center on March 17, 2011.

At DWF3, deaf, hard of hearing and hearing people get together to celebrate their deafness and culture. There's plenty of social opportunities, broomball tournament, exhibition booths, and VIP dinner. We're loaded with deaf awareness for hearing community to learn about deaf and hard of hearing community. DWF3 raises funds for DEAF Inc.'s deaf and hard of hearing programs. We hope that we see you there!

For more information, go to our website:
http://winterfest.deafinc.org

title.$t: DEAF Inc. eNews: Deafilicious Wrap Up and Upcoming Workshops/Events!

media$title.$t: DEAF Inc. eNews: Deafilicious Wrap Up and Upcoming Workshops/Events!

media$description.$t:
The 2nd annual Deafilicious Fashion Benefit has exceeded our expectations! On June 10th, at G.S.L.A.D., many beautiful ladies and handsome men walked on the cat walk and showed off fabulous clothes from Maurice's, Back On Rack, Old Navy, Kohl's and other different clothing stores. The audience enjoyed the show while they ate delicious meal served by San-Sai Japanese Grill.

We raised three times more funds than last year! The funds will go to programs for deaf and hard of hearing people at DEAF Inc. DEAF Inc. wants to thank all of the sponsors, exhibitors, volunteers and attendees who made this fabulous event a huge success!

You can check out pictures from the Deafilicious Fashion Benefit, by visiting DEAF Inc. Facebook page. We hope to  see you all at the next Deafilicious! Go to our Faceboo: http://facebook.com/deafinc

Also, we have more information on our upcoming workshops and events! Please watch our eNews video.

title.$t: DEAF Inc. Special Announcement: The battle is not over for SB188!

media$title.$t: DEAF Inc. Special Announcement: The battle is not over for SB188!

media$description.$t:
The battle is not over for SB188!

Governor Nixon have vetoed Senate Bill (SB) 188 at Old Courthouse in Downtown St. Louis. As of now, SB188 is going back to the Missouri Senate. The Senate has to decide if they want to override Governor Nixon's veto.  You can learn more by watch the signing video or read below.

What is SB 188?

It is a bill that changes that law related to Missouri Human Rights Act and employment discrimination. There are many businesses in Missouri that wants SB 188 to pass. Most of these businesses are not from Missouri. If SB 188 passes, it will make it easier for businesses to get dismissed from discriminating deaf and hard of hearing people.

What's happening with SB 188 right now?

Before Governor Nixon vetoed SB 188, the vote in the Senate was 25 in favor and 9 against. If these Senators continue to vote the same, it will pass and override the Governor's veto in the Senate. An override of a veto requires a 2/3rd votes or 67% of the votes by both the Senate and the House. If it passes the Senate, it still needs to go and be approved by the House, but let's try to prevent this from entering the House by defeating SB 188 in the Senate.

Okay, how do I prevent SB188 from passing in the Senate?

We need to call and convince 3 or more legislators to change their mind and vote against SB 188. We need to get a total of 12 or more Senators to vote against SB 188.  So far, we only 9 Senators voting against SB 188.

We need your help again! We need you to call your local Senator and others to convince them to change their vote. The Senate may vote on this bill anytime within 2 weeks, so call today!

If you don't know who is your local legislator, go to  http://www.senate.mo.gov and type your zip code (with 9 digits).  You will find who is your local legislator in your district.  It is really easy to call his office and say just a few words. Your call and voice do matter!

We hope that this article (or video) helped you fight for your human rights as a deaf and hard of hearing individual. If you have any questions, please contact us at 314-714-6400 or email us at info@deafinc.org.

Call your local Senator today and say
"Vote Nay to SB 188!"

title.$t: DEAF Inc.'s SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT: SB 188

media$title.$t: DEAF Inc.'s SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT: SB 188

media$description.$t:
DEAF Inc.'s SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT 

Right now, there is a bill called SB 188, sitting on Governor Nixon's desk that needs your attention. You can watch the signing video or read below.
 
What is SB 188?
It is a bill that changes that law related to Missouri Human Rights Act and employment discrimination. There are many businesses in Missouri that wants SB188 to pass. Most of these businesses are not from Missouri. If SB188 passes, it will make it easier for businesses to get dismissed from discriminating deaf and hard of hearing people.
 
How to stop SB188?  
Call the governor's office at 573-751-3222 and tell the office that you want Governor Nixon to say no or veto the bill - SB188.  It is really easy to call the office and say just a few words. Your call and voice do matter!  If many of us call his office today, it will get him consider veto SB188.
 
I hope this video helped you to fight for your rights. If you have any questions, please contact us at 314-714-6400 or email us at info@deafinc.org.
